WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.045
Saunders: If I thought
we could get a conviction,

00:03.045 --> 00:04.880
it would be different.

00:04.880 --> 00:06.340
But I am worried about having
enough evidence in this case.

00:06.340 --> 00:08.467
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:08.467 --> 00:10.594
From now on,
I go where you go.

00:10.594 --> 00:12.721
Goodman: We would like to invite
you to be the guest host

00:12.721 --> 00:15.307
while we look for Dr. Stacy's
permanent replacement.

00:15.307 --> 00:17.434
Thank you for letting me
be your Regina.

00:17.434 --> 00:19.269
You've affected me
so deeply.

00:19.269 --> 00:20.646
We've had to shut
our doors,

00:20.646 --> 00:23.774
but our restaurant will be back,
in some way, someday.

00:23.774 --> 00:24.983
Eddie:
This is an agreement

00:24.983 --> 00:27.110
for us to have joint custody
of Theo.

00:27.110 --> 00:29.529
I got a call from
the person who hit me.

00:29.529 --> 00:31.615
I just don't want you to do
something you'll regret.

00:31.615 --> 00:32.824
Maggie:
Did he touch you?

00:32.824 --> 00:34.952
No.
He just touched himself.

00:34.952 --> 00:37.162
Sophie's decided
to go to the police today.

00:37.162 --> 00:39.122
I told him how much
she needed this program,

00:39.122 --> 00:41.833
and he never would have known
any of that if it wasn't for me.
No.

00:41.833 --> 00:43.293
Anybody see you?

00:43.293 --> 00:44.753
No.

00:44.753 --> 00:46.338
Peter: Please!

00:46.338 --> 00:53.929
♪♪

00:53.929 --> 00:55.764
[ Dog barking in distance ]

00:55.764 --> 00:58.517
♪♪

00:58.517 --> 00:59.726
Can I help you?

00:59.726 --> 01:01.395
My name's Gary.

01:01.395 --> 01:03.230
I'm Sophie's...

01:04.856 --> 01:08.151
Her mom left her with me
when she went to France.

01:08.151 --> 01:11.655
So when Peter
did what he did...

01:11.655 --> 01:13.907
♪♪

01:13.907 --> 01:15.576
...that was on my watch.

01:15.576 --> 01:17.703
♪♪

01:17.703 --> 01:20.163
Now, I know
that he hurt your family, too.

01:20.163 --> 01:21.790
Your daughter.

01:23.875 --> 01:26.211
So, are we gonna let him
get away with it?

01:26.211 --> 01:28.213
♪♪

01:36.888 --> 01:38.557
Darcy: Gary?

01:39.891 --> 01:42.019
There you are.
Seems a little formal

01:42.019 --> 01:43.603
to wash my car,
but alright.

01:43.603 --> 01:45.981
Ha‐ha, very funny.
The reason I am wearing this

01:45.981 --> 01:47.482
is because
the Realtor called.

01:47.482 --> 01:49.484
We need to go to Lenox.
Mm.

01:49.484 --> 01:51.611
Turns out, the owner loved
your heartwarming letter.

01:51.611 --> 01:53.280
Mm!

01:53.280 --> 01:54.865
Knew it!

01:54.865 --> 01:56.616
Why didn't I get into letters
instead of numbers?

01:56.616 --> 01:57.868
But we got to
get out there today.

01:57.868 --> 01:59.286
She's got two other
offers already.

01:59.286 --> 02:00.662
Neither
as charming as me.

02:00.662 --> 02:02.539
[ Sniffs, hocks ]

02:02.539 --> 02:03.582
[ Spits ]

02:03.582 --> 02:04.750
Wait a second.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.209
Don't you have
a playdate scheduled

02:06.209 --> 02:07.544
with Theo
and Katherine and Liam?

02:07.544 --> 02:08.712
Already canceled,

02:08.712 --> 02:10.297
and we can go right after
my session with Eddie.

02:10.297 --> 02:12.049
Oh, Eddie can
take a day off.

02:12.049 --> 02:13.925
His upper body's
giving me FOMO.

02:13.925 --> 02:17.471
I know, but I am introducing him
to his new trainer, Russ,

02:17.471 --> 02:18.639
and I want to make sure
that meeting goes well.

02:18.639 --> 02:21.516
And speaking of
great first impressions,

02:21.516 --> 02:23.602
apparently, the owner
is gonna be there today.

02:23.602 --> 02:25.771
So we really need
to live up to your letter.

02:25.771 --> 02:27.898
Why do you think
I'm wearing deodorant?

02:27.898 --> 02:30.567
Hey, if I have to play
the cancer card, I will,

02:30.567 --> 02:33.612
and if I really have to,
I'll show her my one nip.

02:33.612 --> 02:35.947
See, that's what I'm talking
about. No nipple jokes, 'kay?

02:35.947 --> 02:38.367
Fine. I'll cut 'em out.

02:38.367 --> 02:40.118
Just like they
cut out my ni‐‐
Ah‐ah‐ah‐ah‐ah.

02:40.118 --> 02:41.745
Sorry, I'm just getting it
out of my system.

02:41.745 --> 02:43.705
We're very charming,
the two of us.
I know.

02:43.705 --> 02:45.624
Not you and me...

02:45.624 --> 02:46.750
me and my nip.

02:46.750 --> 02:53.131
♪♪

02:53.131 --> 02:55.425
And then just off the top
of the hour, you do your opening

02:55.425 --> 02:58.011
and start taking live calls
for 25 minutes.

02:58.011 --> 02:59.346
Then you'll do
some 15‐second ads

02:59.346 --> 03:01.181
and come back
for your 5‐minute segment.

03:01.181 --> 03:03.600
Hello. It's nice to meet you
in person, too.

03:03.600 --> 03:05.185
I know ‐‐ I'm shorter
than I look on Zoom.

03:05.185 --> 03:06.812
I get it all the time.
Me too.

03:06.812 --> 03:08.480
Sorry. Hi.
Hi.

03:08.480 --> 03:09.564
And then at the half‐hour,

03:09.564 --> 03:11.024
we throw to Nick
for traffic and weather,

03:11.024 --> 03:12.401
and then we do the whole thing
all over again.

03:12.401 --> 03:14.778
Got it.
I better caffeinate.

03:14.778 --> 03:17.572
[ Chuckles nervously ]

03:17.572 --> 03:20.033
I know taking on
an entire show's a lot.

03:20.033 --> 03:21.076
Are you nervous?

03:21.076 --> 03:22.619
Um, more excited, you know?

03:22.619 --> 03:25.539
I have this huge opportunity
every day for the next two weeks

03:25.539 --> 03:27.749
to show
thousands of Bostonians

03:27.749 --> 03:29.543
that asking for help
isn't scary.

03:29.543 --> 03:32.337
It's probably
more like a million.

03:32.337 --> 03:34.256
Some people say
they pick up our station

03:34.256 --> 03:36.049
all the way up
in Nova Scotia.

03:36.049 --> 03:37.551
[ Whimpers ]

03:37.551 --> 03:39.052
Remember a few seconds ago

03:39.052 --> 03:41.096
when I lied
about not being nervous?

03:41.096 --> 03:42.931
You're gonna be great.
[ Sighs ]

03:42.931 --> 03:45.225
And can I just say
thank you?

03:45.225 --> 03:47.310
After five years,
Dr. Stacy never saw me

03:47.310 --> 03:49.521
as more than
her assistant.

03:49.521 --> 03:52.232
But now, thanks to you,
I'm a producer.

03:52.232 --> 03:53.650
I will not let you down.

03:53.650 --> 03:54.776
What's going on
here?

03:54.776 --> 03:56.236
Oh. Hi. I'm Maggie.

03:56.236 --> 03:57.612
I'm the new doc‐‐
That's mine.

03:58.947 --> 04:02.409
Oh. Uh, sor‐‐ I thought
it was a‐a communal situation.

04:02.409 --> 04:04.578
And which is the mug
you brought in?

04:04.578 --> 04:07.789
[ Sighs ]
Uh, I‐I didn't catch your name.

04:07.789 --> 04:11.084
I'm Nick. Traffic and weather
on the hour and the half.

04:11.084 --> 04:13.003
Let's go over some ground rules.

04:13.003 --> 04:16.131
BYOM. You got it.

04:16.131 --> 04:18.967
It's
"Bring Your Own M‐Mug."

04:18.967 --> 04:20.594
Please direct your attention
to the coffee station.

04:20.594 --> 04:22.596
You'll notice
a laminated rules list.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.097
It's next to
the laminated directions

04:24.097 --> 04:25.474
on how to properly load
the dishwasher.

04:25.474 --> 04:27.058
Yeah, see that.
I'm gonna ‐‐

04:27.058 --> 04:28.518
That's smart.
I'll look at all those ‐‐

04:28.518 --> 04:30.645
There's a label maker
in the cabinet above the cups.

04:30.645 --> 04:32.022
There it is!

04:32.022 --> 04:33.982
Labeled "Label Maker."
That's meta.

04:33.982 --> 04:36.067
But you might want to
take a look at your mug,

04:36.067 --> 04:37.944
'cause it says,
"Don't sweat the small stuff."

04:37.944 --> 04:39.654
I don't sweat
the small stuff.

04:40.572 --> 04:43.658
♪♪

04:43.658 --> 04:47.120
As I was saying,
I will not let you down...

04:47.120 --> 04:49.164
starting now.

04:49.164 --> 04:51.625
Oh, the studio.
Let me show you.

04:51.625 --> 04:53.084
[ Sighs ]

04:53.084 --> 04:56.421
And every time another innocent
Black person is killed,

04:56.421 --> 04:58.882
that armor gets heavier
and heavier.

04:58.882 --> 05:03.386
But I've seen what can happen
if we just keep showing up.

05:03.386 --> 05:05.138
♪♪

05:05.138 --> 05:07.474
‐Black lives matter!
‐Black lives matter!

05:07.474 --> 05:14.022
♪♪

05:14.022 --> 05:15.857
Things can change.

05:17.651 --> 05:20.320
So...what do you think?

05:20.320 --> 05:22.739
[ Sighs ]
It's amazing, Rome.

05:24.324 --> 05:27.369
It's exactly what the world
needs right now.

05:27.369 --> 05:28.912
Well, in that case, Shanice,
can you, uh,

05:28.912 --> 05:30.539
quickly become an agent?
'Cause I have a feeling

05:30.539 --> 05:33.208
that my agent's gonna tell me
it's not good enough to sell.

05:33.208 --> 05:34.709
Thank you for making the time,
seriously.

05:34.709 --> 05:36.503
Mm, please.

05:36.503 --> 05:38.421
It's a perfect way
to spend my day off from set.

05:38.421 --> 05:41.091
So much better than being stuck
in yet another hotel room

05:41.091 --> 05:42.801
living off of room service.

05:42.801 --> 05:44.511
Oh, that sounds like hell.

05:44.511 --> 05:45.595
It is.

05:45.595 --> 05:47.222
[ Both laugh ]

05:47.222 --> 05:50.267
Although I'm not sure
Kiana can tell the difference.

05:50.267 --> 05:53.228
I brought her to Boston with me
while I'm shooting this movie,

05:53.228 --> 05:54.437
but I think
she's seen more

05:54.437 --> 05:56.314
of the city she's building
on "Minecraft."

05:56.314 --> 05:58.483
My friend's son Theo
is exact same way.

05:58.483 --> 06:01.069
Caught him trading candy
for screen time. True story.

06:01.069 --> 06:02.571
[ Both chuckle ]

06:02.571 --> 06:04.364
[ Sighing ]

06:04.364 --> 06:06.283
Regina: Hey, babe.
Hey, how'd
the interview go?

06:06.283 --> 06:08.326
[ Scoffs ]

06:08.326 --> 06:10.161
Rome told me about
the restaurant.

06:10.161 --> 06:11.830
Honey, I am so sorry.

06:11.830 --> 06:13.748
Mm, thank you.

06:13.748 --> 06:17.127
And thanks again for giving us
that shout‐out on social media.

06:17.127 --> 06:18.753
It bought us
a couple more months.

06:18.753 --> 06:20.088
Our waiter, Teddy,
burst into tears

06:20.088 --> 06:22.424
when he found out
you did that.

06:22.424 --> 06:24.426
Though he cried most days.
[ Both laugh ]

06:24.426 --> 06:26.011
Well, I wish
I could have done more.

06:26.011 --> 06:29.556
That's okay. Here I am, fresh
off an interview for head chef

06:29.556 --> 06:32.267
at Crocodilze ‐‐
and that is with a "Z" ‐‐

06:32.267 --> 06:35.186
with over 56 locations
between here and Albuquerque.

06:35.186 --> 06:38.648
H‐Hey, one of those locations is
where I spent my 13th birthday.

06:38.648 --> 06:40.108
In fact, Crocodile Keith

06:40.108 --> 06:42.027
delivered my cake
to me personally.

06:42.027 --> 06:43.445
Well, that's exactly
what you want

06:43.445 --> 06:44.446
when you're going through
puberty, right?

06:44.446 --> 06:46.156
You want a restaurant
full of people staring at you

06:46.156 --> 06:49.159
while you're being serenaded to
by a grown man in a lizard suit.

06:49.159 --> 06:50.869
Here comes
the pathetic part.

06:50.869 --> 06:52.037
I don't think they're gonna
offer me the job.

06:52.037 --> 06:53.913
You don't know that.
But I do,

06:53.913 --> 06:56.750
because I said something stupid
about improving the menu,

06:56.750 --> 06:59.085
and when I left, they said,
"We'll be in touch.

06:59.085 --> 07:00.629
What's your e‐mail again?"

07:00.629 --> 07:01.838
Ooh.
Yeah.

07:01.838 --> 07:03.548
No one gets the "you're hired"
over e‐mail.

07:03.548 --> 07:05.175
Mm. But maybe
it's for the best.

07:05.175 --> 07:06.676
I mean, I can't work
in a restaurant

07:06.676 --> 07:08.595
where, when the host
seats you, they say...

07:08.595 --> 07:10.305
"See your waiter,
alligator."
"See your waiter,
alligator."

07:10.305 --> 07:12.223
You know
what's crazy about that is,

07:12.223 --> 07:14.601
an alligator ain't even
the same thing as a crocodile,

07:14.601 --> 07:16.645
which they should know ‐‐
It's their mascot.

07:16.645 --> 07:17.937
[ Laughter ]

07:17.937 --> 07:19.230
Well, I'm gonna go change.

07:20.690 --> 07:22.734
I can't believe
I wore a dress for that.

07:22.734 --> 07:24.944
A cute dress
with pockets.

07:24.944 --> 07:28.698
Ah, apparently I'm not the only
one who could use a day off.

07:28.698 --> 07:31.284
♪♪

07:31.284 --> 07:33.286
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:33.286 --> 07:35.455
♪♪

07:35.455 --> 07:37.248
Man: Hey, we need you
on the register.

07:37.248 --> 07:39.334
Woman: Okay.
Woman #2: Attention,
Halpert's customers...

07:39.334 --> 07:40.794
[ Inhales sharply ]

07:40.794 --> 07:42.295
Halpert's.

07:42.295 --> 07:45.882
♪♪

07:45.882 --> 07:47.884
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

07:47.884 --> 07:49.052
[ Cellphone beeps ]

07:49.052 --> 07:50.095
Hello?

07:50.095 --> 07:51.429
Where are you?

07:51.429 --> 07:53.056
Uh...

07:53.056 --> 07:55.433
I'm, uh, running errands.
Why?

07:55.433 --> 07:57.894
We have a session today,
remember? With Russ?

07:57.894 --> 08:00.146
Ah, I'm sorry.
I forgot.

08:00.146 --> 08:02.607
I lost track of time.
I'll be right there.

08:04.150 --> 08:06.903
Hey. What's your day
look like?

08:06.903 --> 08:09.072
Well, Darcy and Liam
canceled our playdate.

08:09.072 --> 08:11.241
And they're moving
out of town,

08:11.241 --> 08:14.452
so now I'm forced to face
my worst fear,

08:14.452 --> 08:15.995
something that
I've successfully avoided

08:15.995 --> 08:17.872
for the last ten years ‐‐

08:17.872 --> 08:19.165
making new friends.

08:19.165 --> 08:20.959
Well, I think
I can help you out.

08:20.959 --> 08:23.294
[ Chuckles ]
You really think

08:23.294 --> 08:25.630
you can sustain
three hours of enthusiasm

08:25.630 --> 08:28.133
for Theo's
Hogwarts Express Lego set?

08:28.133 --> 08:30.051
Actually, yes.

08:30.051 --> 08:31.094
[ Chuckles ]

08:31.094 --> 08:32.595
Aw, sweet.

08:32.595 --> 08:35.807
But I do have a friend in town
with her 11‐year‐old daughter

08:35.807 --> 08:37.851
who desperately needs a break
from screen time.

08:37.851 --> 08:39.936
Boom, done!

08:39.936 --> 08:42.272
Tell them to swing by whenever.
She can just text me.

08:42.272 --> 08:45.817
Oh, one more thing ‐‐ That
friend is Shanice Williamson.

08:45.817 --> 08:48.486
You know, the actress?

08:48.486 --> 08:50.530
Who was gonna play Regina
in my movie?

08:50.530 --> 08:54.617
Yeah, I‐I‐I know
who Shanice Williamson is.

08:54.617 --> 08:57.287
She wants to ‐‐

08:57.287 --> 08:58.705
She wants to have a playdate
with us?

08:58.705 --> 09:00.498
Mm‐hmm.
Will she be staying,

09:00.498 --> 09:04.252
or is this like a ‐‐ is this
like a drop‐off situation?

09:04.252 --> 09:06.212
Um, it doesn't matter.
I'll plan for both.

09:06.212 --> 09:08.339
Uh, what d‐‐
what does she eat?

09:08.339 --> 09:10.675
I mean, uh,
w‐w‐what should I wear?

09:10.675 --> 09:13.261
Just be yourself.
You will have fun.

09:13.261 --> 09:16.347
"Be myself." Rome, [Scoffs]
that's a recipe for disaster.

09:16.347 --> 09:17.932
I gotta go.

09:17.932 --> 09:19.934
[ Gasps ] Great!
You are perfectly dressed!

09:19.934 --> 09:21.227
Let's go!

09:21.227 --> 09:23.396
Where am I going
that requires sweatpants?

09:23.396 --> 09:25.356
Indoor skydiving.
Remember that gift card

09:25.356 --> 09:26.441
your mom gave us
for our anniversary?

09:26.441 --> 09:28.193
Oh, the one
she re‐gifted us?

09:28.193 --> 09:29.360
Yeah, I do.

09:30.862 --> 09:32.322
Wait, you really
wanna do that?

09:32.322 --> 09:33.656
You know, come on.

09:33.656 --> 09:35.408
You and me,
we just need a day

09:35.408 --> 09:37.869
of having fun and laughing
at whatever happens.

09:37.869 --> 09:40.538
And in this case, it'll be you
being shoved into a giant tube

09:40.538 --> 09:42.707
while an oversized fan
blows you up from the bottom.

09:42.707 --> 09:44.959
So you might want to tighten
the drawstring on those pants.

09:46.669 --> 09:48.421
Come on, come on, come on.
Adventure time.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.048
Come on, let's do it!
Let's do it!

09:50.048 --> 09:51.925
I'm coming. I'm coming.
Come on. Let's go.

09:51.925 --> 09:53.510
Gary:
Alright, dude! Here we go!

09:53.510 --> 09:54.761
One‐time it!

09:54.761 --> 09:57.388
Boom! Boo‐yah!

09:57.388 --> 09:59.307
Dude, you keep that up,
you're gonna have to go pro.

09:59.307 --> 10:01.434
You know that? Forget about
your mom and I buying a house.

10:01.434 --> 10:03.645
You'll be rich enough
to buy it for us.

10:03.645 --> 10:07.315
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

10:07.315 --> 10:10.527
Alright. How you feeling
about this move, dude?

10:10.527 --> 10:12.237
All my friends are here.

10:12.237 --> 10:13.947
I don't know anyone
in Lenox.

10:13.947 --> 10:16.825
You know me. I'm taller
than all your friends,

10:16.825 --> 10:19.077
and I make more money.
Ask anybody.

10:20.995 --> 10:23.540
Look, I know how you feel.

10:23.540 --> 10:25.166
I gotta leave
all my peeps, too,

10:25.166 --> 10:28.169
which is why you and I have to
have each other's backs, right?

10:28.169 --> 10:29.712
Yeah, I guess.

10:31.840 --> 10:33.508
Alright, give me
one more good one.

10:33.508 --> 10:35.301
Let's go.
This is the game‐winner.

10:35.301 --> 10:37.137
Everything's on the line!
One time!

10:38.888 --> 10:48.189
♪♪

10:48.189 --> 10:49.732
I'll tell you what.

10:49.732 --> 10:53.361
Go get us a couple drinks
from that truck, alright?

10:53.361 --> 10:56.489
First rule on the way
to the hockey hall of fame

10:56.489 --> 10:59.033
is that you gotta replenish
those electrolytes.

10:59.033 --> 10:59.826
Liam: Got it.
Alright?

10:59.826 --> 11:01.286
Be right back.

11:01.286 --> 11:03.121
Gary Mendez, right?

11:03.121 --> 11:06.291
We met the other day
at the police station.

11:06.291 --> 11:07.917
You picked a fight
with our garbage can.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.127
Yeah.

11:09.127 --> 11:11.462
Sorry about that.

11:11.462 --> 11:13.089
You didn't have to follow me
all the way out here.

11:13.089 --> 11:14.757
I could have just
Venmo'd you.

11:16.050 --> 11:17.468
Peter Benoit
is in a coma.

11:18.469 --> 11:19.971
Yeah, I heard.

11:19.971 --> 11:21.973
Can't say I'm too broken up
about it.

11:21.973 --> 11:25.310
Well, you were pretty upset
the other day at the station.

11:25.310 --> 11:27.437
Next day,
this guy's in the hospital.

11:27.437 --> 11:29.731
You mind if I ask you
where you were Tuesday night?

11:29.731 --> 11:32.233
Not at all.
I was with my dad.

11:32.233 --> 11:34.194
What time
did you leave there?

11:34.194 --> 11:37.822
Oh, must have been
about 11:45.

11:37.822 --> 11:39.616
It was during Kimmel's
opening monologue,

11:39.616 --> 11:42.160
which is why my pop
only gave me half a hug.

11:42.160 --> 11:44.412
I'm his second‐favorite
guy with a beard.

11:44.412 --> 11:46.122
So, you weren't
at Peter's house?

11:46.122 --> 11:47.665
I don't even know
where that guy lives.

11:49.667 --> 11:53.671
Oh, uh, I just, uh,
drove by your condo.

11:53.671 --> 11:56.007
There's a "For Sale"
sign out front.

11:56.007 --> 11:59.344
Yeah, my girlfriend
got transferred to Lenox.

11:59.344 --> 12:00.970
Berkshires.

12:00.970 --> 12:02.722
Nice escape
from the big city.

12:04.599 --> 12:07.185
Listen, man, if you think I did
this, just call my dad, okay?

12:07.185 --> 12:09.771
I was with him all night. We
watched, uh, "Wheel of Fortune,"

12:09.771 --> 12:12.106
a little "Jeopardy!",
played some online poker.

12:12.106 --> 12:15.360
Ah, I don't need to call him.
I'm sure you were.

12:15.360 --> 12:18.196
You understand
I'm just covering the bases.

12:18.196 --> 12:20.531
Eventually,
this guy's gonna wake up,

12:20.531 --> 12:24.118
and when he does, he can tell us
himself what happened.

12:24.118 --> 12:26.746
And if he doesn't
wake up, well,

12:26.746 --> 12:29.624
that just makes things
a lot more complicated.

12:29.624 --> 12:34.712
♪♪

12:34.712 --> 12:37.715
Fuel up,
'cause you're going down!

12:37.715 --> 12:41.469
♪♪

12:45.723 --> 12:47.433
So, yeah, we're pretty good
with these, right?

12:47.433 --> 12:49.852
He's gonna love you.

12:49.852 --> 12:53.106
Really? He has
no redeeming qualities?

12:53.106 --> 12:54.315
Yeah, I don't understand
why you'd work with,

12:54.315 --> 12:56.234
let alone be friends with,
someone who ‐‐

12:56.234 --> 12:58.569
Hey, you must be Eddie.

12:58.569 --> 12:59.862
Well, on the plus side,

12:59.862 --> 13:02.615
now I feel no pressure
to have any redeeming qualities.

13:02.615 --> 13:04.284
Mm.
Eddie, this is Russ.

13:04.284 --> 13:06.536
Hey, Russ.
It's nice to meet ‐‐

13:06.536 --> 13:07.745
Um ‐‐

13:09.872 --> 13:11.249
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

13:11.249 --> 13:12.542
You didn't tell me
this guy's in a wheelchair.

13:12.542 --> 13:14.877
I may have to charge extra.

13:14.877 --> 13:16.504
I am sorry.

13:16.504 --> 13:18.339
I just ‐‐

13:18.339 --> 13:21.009
You know,
I wasn't expecting...

13:21.009 --> 13:24.262
And now I guess I'm getting
a taste of my own medicine.

13:24.262 --> 13:25.680
Could have used
a heads‐up.

13:25.680 --> 13:28.433
Then I would have missed
this incredible moment.

13:28.433 --> 13:29.475
[ Sighs ]

13:29.475 --> 13:35.857
♪♪

13:35.857 --> 13:38.026
[ Clears throat ]

13:38.026 --> 13:40.069
So, she's in, like,
movies and stuff?

13:40.069 --> 13:43.406
Uh, yes, but it's
really important

13:43.406 --> 13:46.492
that we ‐‐ we treat her
like an ordinary person.

13:46.492 --> 13:47.118
Got it.

13:48.453 --> 13:50.955
Are you wearing
shoulder pads?

13:51.873 --> 13:53.249
[ Doorbell rings ]

13:53.249 --> 13:54.417
Uh...

13:58.212 --> 14:00.965
Hello! Welcome.

14:00.965 --> 14:03.885
Thanks so much for having us.
I'm Shanice, and this is Kiana.

14:03.885 --> 14:05.553
This is Theo.

14:05.553 --> 14:07.972
Theo: Hi.
Come in!

14:07.972 --> 14:11.225
Oh. Should we
take our shoes off?

14:11.225 --> 14:13.603
Uh, no.
Um, y‐you're fine.

14:13.603 --> 14:16.355
Uh, I‐I just
have, um, mine off

14:16.355 --> 14:18.608
because, um, I...

14:18.608 --> 14:20.234
I had on some heels

14:20.234 --> 14:22.987
[Chuckles]
that were killing me.

14:22.987 --> 14:25.490
W‐We never wear shoes
in the house.

14:25.490 --> 14:27.200
Even when we got
the new dishwasher,

14:27.200 --> 14:28.910
she made the guy
wear booties.

14:28.910 --> 14:31.913
[ Chuckles ]
No, it ‐‐ You're fine.

14:31.913 --> 14:35.374
And if, by any chance, you're
into Harry Potter and Legos,

14:35.374 --> 14:37.335
there's a Hogwarts Express
waiting for you.

14:37.335 --> 14:38.795
Mom!

14:38.795 --> 14:41.089
I used to play with Legos
in like fourth grade.

14:41.089 --> 14:43.633
Oh, that's too bad.
I love Legos.

14:43.633 --> 14:45.051
Really?

14:45.051 --> 14:47.053
Yeah, and I'm a total
Potterhead.

14:48.096 --> 14:50.598
Uh, right this way.

14:50.598 --> 14:53.309
Wait, she said "Pot‐ ter
head," right?

14:53.309 --> 14:54.519
[ Laughs awkwardly ]

14:54.519 --> 14:56.229
[ Chuckles ]

14:56.229 --> 14:59.273
Um, this is a ‐‐
it's a safe space here.

14:59.273 --> 15:01.150
We're all Potterheads.

15:01.150 --> 15:03.277
Not by choice.
It chooses us.

15:03.277 --> 15:05.738
♪♪

15:05.738 --> 15:07.490
Can I get you a drink?

15:07.490 --> 15:09.951
♪♪

15:09.951 --> 15:11.869
Maggie: [ On radio ] And while
this show is not a substitute

15:11.869 --> 15:13.871
for in‐person therapy,

15:13.871 --> 15:17.333
my promise to you is I will
spend all the time it takes

15:17.333 --> 15:21.295
to make each listener
feel heard and understood.

15:21.295 --> 15:24.590
And if your challenge
requires more than that,

15:24.590 --> 15:26.592
I will point you
in the right direction.

15:26.592 --> 15:30.513
So, if you are just looking
for quick sound bites

15:30.513 --> 15:33.975
which are really just for
ratings, you should skip this,

15:33.975 --> 15:39.438
because Maggie is here,
and therapy is nothing to fear.

15:39.438 --> 15:42.859
That sounded better when I said
it to the mirror this morning.

15:42.859 --> 15:45.486
Okay, our lines are open,

15:45.486 --> 15:48.281
and for our first caller,
we have...

15:48.281 --> 15:50.491
Theresa from
North Andover.

15:50.491 --> 15:53.661
Theresa, you are
In the Room With Dr. Bloom.

15:53.661 --> 15:56.038
Theresa: [ Boston accent ]
I got a problem, Dr. Bloom.

15:56.038 --> 15:58.457
When I fart,
it makes me cry.

15:58.457 --> 15:59.500
[ Fart ]

15:59.500 --> 16:01.335
[ Imitating sobbing ]

16:01.335 --> 16:05.464
Yeah, that's ‐‐
that's very funny.

16:05.464 --> 16:08.509
But, in actuality,
there can be a link

16:08.509 --> 16:12.388
between our emotions
and good gut health.

16:12.388 --> 16:16.559
Now, if we have any actual...

16:16.559 --> 16:17.852
questions...

16:19.687 --> 16:20.771
[ Car horn beeps ]

16:20.771 --> 16:22.523
[ Chuckles ] Wow.

16:22.523 --> 16:24.567
Wow!
[ Both laughing ]

16:24.567 --> 16:27.612
I can't believe people pay
to ride an industrial fan.

16:27.612 --> 16:29.322
I want to take the person
who opened that place

16:29.322 --> 16:31.532
and throw him
from a real plane.

16:31.532 --> 16:33.201
[ Laughs ]

16:33.201 --> 16:34.869
I'm sorry, baby.
I really thought

16:34.869 --> 16:37.455
it was gonna be
a lot more fun.
Who said it wasn't fun?

16:37.455 --> 16:39.916
Now let's go home and pretend
to surf in the bathtub.

16:39.916 --> 16:41.709
[ Chuckles ]

16:41.709 --> 16:44.170
[ Sighs ]
I got a better idea.

16:44.170 --> 16:50.676
♪♪

16:50.676 --> 16:52.637
Cheryl, you have
a beautiful home.

16:52.637 --> 16:54.305
Oh, thank you.

16:54.305 --> 16:57.099
It's more space than I need
now that Arthur's gone.

16:57.099 --> 17:00.269
And according to my son,
I am not fit to live alone,

17:00.269 --> 17:02.480
so I'm gonna end up living
in his guest house

17:02.480 --> 17:04.732
with my unemployed
granddaughter.

17:06.192 --> 17:07.443
Fig cookie?

17:07.443 --> 17:11.197
♪♪

17:11.197 --> 17:12.240
Come on.

17:12.240 --> 17:14.575
Wow. I love these.

17:14.575 --> 17:16.410
Those are my
"timeless treasures."

17:16.410 --> 17:18.746
You got that right.

17:18.746 --> 17:22.792
Uh, this ‐‐
Uh, that's the one
my granddaughter made.

17:22.792 --> 17:24.168
It's extra special.

17:24.168 --> 17:26.212
It sure is.
I mean, what's going on?

17:26.212 --> 17:28.339
Is she opening the umbrella?
Is she closing it?

17:28.339 --> 17:31.300
Is the rain about to fall?
Is the sun coming back out?

17:31.300 --> 17:32.635
I guess we'll never know.

17:32.635 --> 17:34.011
She's opening it.

17:34.011 --> 17:36.639
Oh.
I guess we know.

17:36.639 --> 17:38.266
Cheryl, do you mind
showing me

17:38.266 --> 17:40.351
the, uh, light fixtures
in the kitchen?

17:40.351 --> 17:42.311
They were so beautiful.

17:42.311 --> 17:44.480
Regina: So, this
is your better idea?

17:44.480 --> 17:45.773
Rome:
Yeah, I knew it was a sign

17:45.773 --> 17:48.192
when I saw that huge crocodile
across the parking lot.

17:48.192 --> 17:49.694
This is where
we're gonna have fun.

17:49.694 --> 17:51.821
No, the only thing we're getting
here is a stomachache.

17:51.821 --> 17:53.114
You see, that's what
I'm talking about.

17:53.114 --> 17:55.658
We hate‐watched the final season
of "Game of Thrones,"

17:55.658 --> 17:58.995
and we are going to hate‐eat
at Crocodilze with a "Z."

17:58.995 --> 18:00.746
[ Scoffs ]

18:00.746 --> 18:02.415
[ Both sigh ]

18:02.415 --> 18:04.792
See your waiter,
alligator.

18:04.792 --> 18:07.211
♪♪

18:07.211 --> 18:08.671
Restaurant bullies.
I'm in.

18:08.671 --> 18:09.839
[ Both laugh ]

18:09.839 --> 18:11.173
[ Beatboxing ]

18:11.173 --> 18:12.425
[ Laughs ]

18:17.179 --> 18:18.806
Oh, no.
What are we gonna do?

18:18.806 --> 18:19.724
Shh, shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh.

18:19.724 --> 18:20.975
Don't worry.

18:20.975 --> 18:23.477
I got your back, right?

18:23.477 --> 18:25.229
Darcy: Gary, do you want
to see the bedrooms?

18:25.229 --> 18:29.191
Uh, actually,
I need to see the bathroom.

18:29.191 --> 18:30.234
[ Chuckles ]

18:30.234 --> 18:32.653
It's the most important room
in the house,

18:32.653 --> 18:34.030
am I right?

18:34.030 --> 18:38.868
♪♪

18:38.868 --> 18:40.786
[ Sighs ]

18:40.786 --> 18:46.167
♪♪

18:46.167 --> 18:49.462
[ Peter grunting ]
Shh.

18:49.462 --> 18:51.631
Peter: Take anything you want.
There's some money in the safe.

18:51.631 --> 18:53.049
We don't want your money.

18:53.049 --> 18:54.550
We're here because
we know what you did.

18:54.550 --> 18:56.093
I‐I don't know ‐‐ I‐I don't know
what you're talking about.

18:56.093 --> 18:58.179
Yeah, you do.
And if I were you,

18:58.179 --> 18:59.555
I would start telling the truth
right now.

18:59.555 --> 19:01.223
I am. I swear.
Hey!

19:02.683 --> 19:05.311
I want to hear you say
what you did to those girls.

19:05.311 --> 19:06.646
Girls?
W‐What ‐‐ What girls?

19:06.646 --> 19:08.689
I‐I don't know
what you're talking about.

19:08.689 --> 19:11.609
♪♪

19:11.609 --> 19:13.402
Please!
Okay, don't hurt me.

19:13.402 --> 19:14.612
Please.

19:14.612 --> 19:16.113
Next time,
I do that to your head!

19:16.113 --> 19:17.698
Peter: Okay, okay, fine.
Fine, fine, fine.

19:17.698 --> 19:21.744
I had a couple of students
come over here in bathing suits.

19:21.744 --> 19:25.164
A few times, things might have
gone a little too far.

19:25.164 --> 19:27.083
But I didn't hurt them,
I swear.

19:27.083 --> 19:28.584
What about Layla?

19:28.584 --> 19:31.128
♪♪

19:31.128 --> 19:32.922
Peter:
Hey, I‐I can't see you,

19:32.922 --> 19:34.590
so I‐I don't know
who you are.

19:34.590 --> 19:37.176
I want you...
to look at me!

19:38.761 --> 19:40.513
No, I'm not looking.

19:40.513 --> 19:42.598
I can't see you.

19:42.598 --> 19:44.392
I want you to look at me

19:44.392 --> 19:47.561
and tell me what you did
to my daughter.

19:47.561 --> 19:52.817
♪♪

19:52.817 --> 19:54.610
[ Knock on door ]

19:54.610 --> 19:57.571
Darcy:
You okay in there?

19:57.571 --> 20:00.282
[ Water running ]
Just checking
the water pressure!

20:01.909 --> 20:03.411
[ Water shuts off ]

20:03.411 --> 20:04.912
♪♪

20:09.166 --> 20:10.835
[ British accent ] Shall we take
our Butterbeers to go?

20:10.835 --> 20:12.253
We shall.

20:12.253 --> 20:18.592
♪♪

20:18.592 --> 20:21.721
I'm sorry. I should have made
something more sophisticated.

20:21.721 --> 20:22.972
Are you kidding?

20:22.972 --> 20:25.307
Floppy, greasy pizza's
my jam.

20:25.307 --> 20:26.892
[ Chuckles ]

20:26.892 --> 20:29.687
Same.

20:29.687 --> 20:32.940
"I want you
in all my tomorrows."

20:32.940 --> 20:35.109
What?

20:35.109 --> 20:37.695
From "Clear Water Down."

20:37.695 --> 20:39.280
You know, the final scene,
when you ‐‐

20:39.280 --> 20:40.781
you pull your husband
from the water

20:40.781 --> 20:43.492
and you bring him back
with CPR?

20:43.492 --> 20:45.536
Oh. Right.

20:45.536 --> 20:46.746
Great memory.

20:46.746 --> 20:48.038
[ Laughs ]

20:49.373 --> 20:50.666
I'm sorry.

20:50.666 --> 20:53.669
I know I've been acting
like a weirdo.

20:53.669 --> 20:55.129
I just have to admit ‐‐

20:55.129 --> 20:57.173
I am a huge fan.

20:57.173 --> 20:58.674
I was obsessed
with "Days of Our Lives"

20:58.674 --> 20:59.717
during law school.

20:59.717 --> 21:01.677
I loved your character,

21:01.677 --> 21:05.055
and I was so sad when
the bee swarm took you out.

21:05.055 --> 21:06.599
[ Sighs ]
I sound so dumb.

21:06.599 --> 21:08.142
Not at all.

21:08.142 --> 21:09.810
I appreciate it.

21:09.810 --> 21:11.187
I was obsessed
with the show, too,

21:11.187 --> 21:13.063
before I booked the role.

21:13.063 --> 21:14.356
When I first met
Deidre Hall,

21:14.356 --> 21:17.067
I could barely even
make eye contact.

21:17.067 --> 21:20.112
I told her
it was nice to meet me, too.

21:20.112 --> 21:23.115
[ Both laugh ]

21:23.115 --> 21:25.284
I was so stressed out
about meeting you.

21:25.284 --> 21:27.578
See those flowers?
I‐I moved them four times.

21:27.578 --> 21:30.289
And let me guess ‐‐
you are a shoe‐free home?

21:30.289 --> 21:31.916
[ Sighs ]
Theo was so confused.

21:31.916 --> 21:34.919
[ Laughs ]

21:34.919 --> 21:36.253
Oh, no,
you can leave them on.

21:36.253 --> 21:37.880
Absolutely not.

21:37.880 --> 21:39.173
I appreciate
your honesty.

21:39.173 --> 21:40.508
I am not
some fragile diva.

21:40.508 --> 21:42.510
I can abide
by the rules of the house.

21:42.510 --> 21:44.929
I assume you have some
Prada slippers I can borrow?

21:44.929 --> 21:46.138
Um...

21:46.138 --> 21:47.723
I'm kidding.

21:47.723 --> 21:49.642
[ Both laugh ]

21:49.642 --> 21:51.352
Look at your face!

21:55.314 --> 21:56.816
Mmm.

21:56.816 --> 21:58.234
That looks so gross.

21:58.234 --> 22:02.238
What's gross
is how delicious it is.

22:02.238 --> 22:04.448
The four‐cheese blend
is perfect.

22:04.448 --> 22:06.700
Caramelized onions
don't overpower,

22:06.700 --> 22:09.328
and there's a hint
of Dijon.

22:09.328 --> 22:11.914
Dijon. Why didn't
I ever think of that?

22:11.914 --> 22:13.415
Well, if it makes you feel
any better,

22:13.415 --> 22:14.750
the chicken Parm ‐‐
terrible.

22:14.750 --> 22:15.918
Mm, mm‐hmm.

22:15.918 --> 22:17.044
You don't have to lie ‐‐

22:17.044 --> 22:18.796
you're practically
inhaling it.

22:18.796 --> 22:22.174
Well, in that case,
you gotta try this.

22:22.174 --> 22:23.634
Take a bite ‐‐
little one, okay?

22:23.634 --> 22:24.969
I need this stuff.
Mm‐hmm.

22:26.971 --> 22:28.138
Mmm.
Mm‐hmm.

22:28.138 --> 22:29.181
Mmm.

22:29.181 --> 22:30.474
Mmm.

22:30.474 --> 22:32.518
We can't even hate‐eat
at this place.

22:32.518 --> 22:34.061
I'm sorry, babe.

22:34.061 --> 22:35.062
Mm‐hmm.

22:35.062 --> 22:36.230
This was a bad idea.

22:36.230 --> 22:38.440
Yeah, it really was.

22:38.440 --> 22:41.402
But that's okay,
'cause I got my revenge.

22:41.402 --> 22:42.820
I told the hostess
it's your birthday.

22:42.820 --> 22:44.029
You didn't.

22:44.029 --> 22:46.532
See your waiter,
alligator.

22:46.532 --> 22:48.075
Together:
♪ We swung from jungle vines ♪

22:48.075 --> 22:49.785
♪ We slithered river miles ♪

22:49.785 --> 22:51.161
♪ To wish you happy birthday ♪

22:51.161 --> 22:53.664
♪ From crocodilze smilez, hey! ♪

22:53.664 --> 22:54.498
Smile.

22:56.333 --> 22:57.668
Well‐played, Gina.

22:57.668 --> 22:58.878
[ Laughs ]

22:58.878 --> 23:00.170
[ Laughs ]

23:00.170 --> 23:01.755
Gina?!

23:01.755 --> 23:03.340
Teddy?

23:03.340 --> 23:04.425
Crocodile Keith?

23:04.425 --> 23:06.552
Oh. Oh.

23:06.552 --> 23:07.970
29...

23:10.180 --> 23:11.348
...and 30.
[ Grunts ]

23:11.348 --> 23:13.434
Darcy wasn't kidding
when she said you were tough.

23:13.434 --> 23:16.770
Oh, so, there were some
compliments thrown in there?

23:16.770 --> 23:18.063
[ Chuckles ]

23:18.063 --> 23:19.315
What else did she say
about me?

23:19.315 --> 23:21.191
Well, that you got
this killer ass

23:21.191 --> 23:23.444
that no one gets to see
anymore.
[ Laughs ]

23:23.444 --> 23:24.486
Alright, she may not have
said that part,

23:24.486 --> 23:26.530
but she thought it.
She definitely thought it.

23:26.530 --> 23:27.781
[ Chuckles ]

23:27.781 --> 23:30.326
So, uh...

23:30.326 --> 23:32.161
how did you end up
in there?

23:32.161 --> 23:33.537
Wow. That's personal.

23:33.537 --> 23:35.122
We've only known each other
for, like, what, five minutes?

23:35.122 --> 23:36.832
I'm sorry, I didn't ‐‐

23:36.832 --> 23:39.126
Hey, I'm messing with you.

23:39.126 --> 23:40.210
Yeah.
I'm an open book.

23:40.210 --> 23:42.004
Tell you what ‐‐
you give me a few more,

23:42.004 --> 23:44.840
I'll tell you
the whole sob story.

23:44.840 --> 23:46.008
Okay.

23:48.093 --> 23:49.929
[ Straining ]
Yep.

23:49.929 --> 23:52.681
So, uh, what was it, huh?

23:52.681 --> 23:55.309
Car? Bus?

23:55.309 --> 23:57.102
Evil Knievel stunt
gone wrong?

23:57.102 --> 23:59.146
Mnh‐mnh.
Much more exciting...

23:59.146 --> 24:00.189
step‐ladder.

24:02.441 --> 24:03.609
What?

24:05.819 --> 24:08.822
I was changing a light bulb
at my girlfriend's place,

24:08.822 --> 24:11.700
and I could have sworn
that thing had only two steps.

24:11.700 --> 24:15.746
I took a step back to
what I thought was the
ground, but it wasn't,

24:15.746 --> 24:17.498
and I felt something snap
in my back.

24:17.498 --> 24:19.833
I tried to walk it off
for a couple hours.

24:19.833 --> 24:22.836
Two days later, I couldn't feel
anything from the waist down.

24:24.296 --> 24:25.297
That was it.

24:27.800 --> 24:30.177
You know, I don't tell everyone
the real story

24:30.177 --> 24:32.805
'cause they're always
just disappointed.

24:32.805 --> 24:35.557
I mean, it's not as sexy
as a hit‐and‐run.

24:35.557 --> 24:38.435
[ Chuckles ]

24:38.435 --> 24:41.271
Well, at least you know
who to be angry at.

24:41.271 --> 24:43.941
Who's that?

24:43.941 --> 24:46.235
Guy who doesn't know
how to use a step‐ladder.

24:46.235 --> 24:47.653
Oh.

24:47.653 --> 24:48.988
Alright.

24:48.988 --> 24:50.489
Okay.
If that's how it's gonna be.

24:50.489 --> 24:53.450
Hey, next time,
maybe use a crosswalk?

24:53.450 --> 24:54.451
I don't know.

24:54.451 --> 24:55.869
Okay, we're done.
We're done!

24:55.869 --> 24:57.746
Oh, no ‐‐ we are done
when I say we're done.

24:57.746 --> 25:00.290
Left hand this time.
A‐five, six, seven, eight.

25:01.417 --> 25:02.668
Can't you just see it?

25:02.668 --> 25:04.545
A crib
could go over here ‐‐

25:04.545 --> 25:06.171
hypothetically speaking,
of course.

25:06.171 --> 25:07.715
But I could totally
see it.

25:07.715 --> 25:08.841
Before it's the baby's room,

25:08.841 --> 25:10.175
it could be
the makin'‐babies room.

25:10.175 --> 25:11.260
Ooh.

25:11.260 --> 25:12.302
[ Both laugh ]

25:12.302 --> 25:13.637
Uh...

25:13.637 --> 25:15.639
are there broken shards
of glass in your pocket,

25:15.639 --> 25:16.849
or are you just happy
to see me?

25:16.849 --> 25:18.183
Um ‐‐ Uh ‐‐

25:18.183 --> 25:21.145
Oh, my God.
What happened?

25:21.145 --> 25:24.523
[ Whispering ] Liam knocked
over the very special one.

25:24.523 --> 25:26.108
Okay, so, that's why you were
acting weird in the bathroom.

25:26.108 --> 25:27.901
Don't worry.
Cheryl didn't see.

25:27.901 --> 25:29.445
I covered for him.

25:29.445 --> 25:31.613
You "covered" for him?

25:31.613 --> 25:34.992
Well, when I say it,
it sounds way cooler.

25:34.992 --> 25:37.745
He's my bud.
I gotta have his back.

25:37.745 --> 25:39.538
I know that you want
to be Liam's friend,

25:39.538 --> 25:42.416
and I appreciate that
you were trying to protect him,

25:42.416 --> 25:45.335
but sometimes that means helping
him face the consequences,

25:45.335 --> 25:47.004
no matter how scary.

25:47.004 --> 25:49.256
And that's not just for Liam ‐‐
that's for any child

25:49.256 --> 25:51.258
that we bring
into this world.

25:51.258 --> 25:52.509
Do you know what I mean?

25:52.509 --> 25:54.136
I do now.

25:54.136 --> 25:55.763
[ Clears
throat ]

25:55.763 --> 25:58.015
Did you know your son broke
one of my figurines?

25:58.015 --> 25:59.975
Yes,
and we are very sorry.

25:59.975 --> 26:03.353
Don't be. I've been looking at
that hideous thing for 20 years.

26:03.353 --> 26:05.731
I've never had an excuse
to get rid of it until now.

26:05.731 --> 26:09.777
More importantly,
he came and apologized.

26:09.777 --> 26:12.488
That kind of honesty
is very rare.

26:12.488 --> 26:14.740
Well, trust me,
he gets it all from her.

26:14.740 --> 26:17.284
Well, whatever you're doing
to raise such a great son,

26:17.284 --> 26:20.871
I want you to keep doing it ‐‐
in this house.

26:20.871 --> 26:22.289
It's yours.
No way.

26:22.289 --> 26:24.458
Oh, my God!
Thank you so much.

26:24.458 --> 26:27.336
Oh, my God!
[ Laughs ]
Ahhh!

26:27.336 --> 26:29.838
Cheryl, get over here.
Come on, you're changing lives.

26:29.838 --> 26:30.964
Let's do this.

26:30.964 --> 26:32.549
Ohhh!

26:32.549 --> 26:33.801
Ow.

26:35.177 --> 26:36.220
I'm sorry.

26:36.220 --> 26:38.013
I'm just so happy.

26:38.013 --> 26:39.598
Man:
There was this woman,

26:39.598 --> 26:41.850
and we were together
every single day.

26:41.850 --> 26:44.103
And then,
she was just gone.

26:44.103 --> 26:46.063
Her name was Dr. Stacy,

26:46.063 --> 26:47.606
and she got replaced
by an uptight ‐‐

26:47.606 --> 26:48.649
I thought
we screen these.

26:48.649 --> 26:50.234
Oh, we do.

26:50.234 --> 26:52.569
He said he was calling
about abandonment issues.

26:52.569 --> 26:54.113
Two minutes
to traffic and weather.

26:55.739 --> 26:57.157
Alright.

26:57.157 --> 26:58.992
I get it.
I'm the new kid.

26:58.992 --> 27:00.577
You're hazing me.

27:00.577 --> 27:02.830
But you should know
that I started a new school

27:02.830 --> 27:05.082
at 9 years old with headgear
and a back brace,

27:05.082 --> 27:07.709
so bring it.

27:07.709 --> 27:10.087
You're In The Room
With Dr. Bloom.

27:10.087 --> 27:11.213
Boy: Hi.

27:11.213 --> 27:13.799
Um, am I on?

27:13.799 --> 27:15.384
Yeah, alright,
who's this?

27:15.384 --> 27:16.927
Is this, uh, Seymour Butts
["see more butts"]

27:16.927 --> 27:18.679
or Ivana Tinkle,
["I wanna tinkle"]

27:18.679 --> 27:20.347
which ‐‐
Oh, no.

27:20.347 --> 27:22.933
My name is Jonah ‐‐
Jonah St. ‐‐

27:22.933 --> 27:24.601
Oh, d‐‐ Uh, no.
Don't say your name.

27:24.601 --> 27:26.478
I'm so sorry.

27:26.478 --> 27:28.146
Uh...

27:28.146 --> 27:29.690
go ahead, Jonah.

27:29.690 --> 27:31.275
Okay.

27:31.275 --> 27:35.070
I‐I called
because I'm scared.

27:35.070 --> 27:36.947
What is scaring you?

27:36.947 --> 27:38.949
My mom drinks a lot.

27:38.949 --> 27:41.118
Sometimes she drives.

27:41.118 --> 27:43.579
Jonah,
are you safe right now?

27:43.579 --> 27:45.289
Yeah.

27:45.289 --> 27:47.499
My mom's at work.

27:47.499 --> 27:49.376
I'm home
with my brother and uncle.

27:49.376 --> 27:50.919
They don't know
I'm calling.

27:50.919 --> 27:52.462
I see.

27:52.462 --> 27:55.090
And are you ever in the car
with your mom

27:55.090 --> 27:56.925
when she's been drinking?

27:56.925 --> 28:00.178
She doesn't drive with us
in the car...

28:00.178 --> 28:01.972
but I want her
to be safe, too.

28:01.972 --> 28:03.849
Of course you do.

28:03.849 --> 28:05.392
Have you told her that?

28:05.392 --> 28:07.853
Once.
It made her cry.

28:07.853 --> 28:09.605
She gets sad a lot.

28:09.605 --> 28:11.106
But when she's happy,

28:11.106 --> 28:13.025
she's the best mom
in the world.

28:13.025 --> 28:15.777
It must be hard not to know
which person you're gonna get.

28:15.777 --> 28:19.197
[ Sniffles ] It is.

28:19.197 --> 28:23.577
Well, I want you to know
that you've done nothing wrong,

28:23.577 --> 28:27.706
and what is going on with her
is not your fault.

28:27.706 --> 28:30.417
We all need help sometimes,
and your mom is no different.

28:30.417 --> 28:32.336
How do I get her help?

28:32.336 --> 28:34.963
Well, you reaching out
is a great first step.

28:34.963 --> 28:37.049
I'm proud of you.

28:37.049 --> 28:41.678
Maggie, it's time
for traffic and weather.

28:41.678 --> 28:44.097
Jonah, is there another adult
in your life

28:44.097 --> 28:45.599
you feel safe
talking to?

28:45.599 --> 28:47.851
Uh, maybe my uncle?

28:51.063 --> 28:53.357
Jonah,
d‐don't go anywhere.

28:53.357 --> 28:54.983
For our listeners,
you're gonna have to wait

28:54.983 --> 28:58.320
to the next half‐hour for
your weather and traffic report.

28:58.320 --> 28:59.696
[ Click ]

28:59.696 --> 29:00.989
You can't do that.

29:00.989 --> 29:02.074
Hello?

29:02.074 --> 29:03.533
Are you there?

29:03.533 --> 29:05.369
Yes, I am here, Jonah.

29:05.369 --> 29:07.496
Don't worry,
I'm not going anywhere.

29:07.496 --> 29:11.124
♪♪

29:11.124 --> 29:12.209
[ Door slams ]

29:18.674 --> 29:20.092
Ah, wow.

29:20.092 --> 29:21.468
It is so good
to see you guys.

29:21.468 --> 29:23.303
Ah, you too, Teddy.

29:23.303 --> 29:25.889
And Happy Birthday,
by the way.

29:25.889 --> 29:26.765
I never knew
you were a Leo!

29:26.765 --> 29:28.225
I'm an Aries!

29:28.225 --> 29:29.851
That explains
why we always got along so well.

29:29.851 --> 29:31.269
A‐Actually, it's not.

29:31.269 --> 29:32.479
Totally...

29:33.772 --> 29:35.315
It's not his birthday.

29:35.315 --> 29:36.984
Oh.

29:36.984 --> 29:38.777
To be honest...

29:38.777 --> 29:40.737
I had an interview
this morning

29:40.737 --> 29:42.489
at the Crocodilze
across town,

29:42.489 --> 29:45.450
and, uh, didn't seem like
they were that into me,

29:45.450 --> 29:47.119
so we came here
to be brats about it.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.998
Yeah, sorry.
I know, that's not cool.

29:50.998 --> 29:52.833
No, no, no, no.
I get it.

29:52.833 --> 29:54.835
And, look, this place isn't
as fancy as Someday,

29:54.835 --> 29:55.627
but it's a gig.

29:55.627 --> 29:57.337
And right now,

29:57.337 --> 29:59.506
I'm just happy
with the steady paycheck.

29:59.506 --> 30:01.717
But they make you do double duty
as Crocodile Keith.

30:01.717 --> 30:02.634
That's pretty rough.

30:02.634 --> 30:04.136
"Make me"?

30:04.136 --> 30:06.471
No, I‐I asked
if I could be Crocodile Keith.

30:06.471 --> 30:07.889
Oh.
Yeah!

30:07.889 --> 30:09.141
I get to come out here
for all the birthdays

30:09.141 --> 30:11.435
and put a smile
on people's faces.

30:11.435 --> 30:15.480
I mean, it's why I got into
hospitality in the first place.

30:15.480 --> 30:18.525
And, hey, the Crocodilze
across town does suck.

30:20.610 --> 30:23.905
But, um, one of my roommates
is a manager here.

30:23.905 --> 30:27.367
So, if you want in,
I can make it happen.

30:27.367 --> 30:29.619
And by the way,
the employee discount here is...

30:29.619 --> 30:32.205
[Singsong voice]
insane!

30:33.373 --> 30:34.541
Hmm.

30:36.168 --> 30:39.337
Your husband had a baby
with another woman?

30:39.337 --> 30:41.339
No wonder you stopped watching
"Days of Our Lives."

30:41.339 --> 30:43.759
You had all the soap opera
you needed in real life.

30:43.759 --> 30:45.385
[ Both laugh ]

30:45.385 --> 30:46.970
Well, at least my divorce
didn't end up

30:46.970 --> 30:49.014
on the cover
of Us Weekly.

30:49.014 --> 30:50.182
[ Laughs ]

30:50.182 --> 30:52.100
Not that I read
that trash.

30:52.100 --> 30:54.061
Only when
I'm at the salon.

30:54.061 --> 30:55.562
And the doctor.

30:55.562 --> 30:56.480
And the dentist.

30:56.480 --> 30:58.482
[ Laughs ]

30:58.482 --> 31:00.776
Well, with Dennis and me,

31:00.776 --> 31:03.320
it wasn't as dramatic
as those tabloids made it look.

31:04.821 --> 31:07.032
He's a great dad.

31:07.032 --> 31:10.786
But I knew I was only staying
in it for Kiana.

31:10.786 --> 31:12.871
Eventually,
she was going to leave,

31:12.871 --> 31:15.123
and he and I would be
two strangers

31:15.123 --> 31:17.626
staring back
at each other.

31:17.626 --> 31:20.629
Do you ever worry
about the story

31:20.629 --> 31:25.467
we're telling our kids about
relationships and commitment?

31:25.467 --> 31:27.094
I mean, my parents stayed
together their whole lives

31:27.094 --> 31:29.137
until my dad passed away.

31:29.137 --> 31:31.181
My parents
are still together...

31:31.181 --> 31:32.891
but they're not happy.

31:32.891 --> 31:36.520
My mom always says,
"A vow is a vow."

31:36.520 --> 31:39.606
Which is why it was so hard
for me to leave Dennis.

31:39.606 --> 31:44.236
But I didn't want to set
that same example for Kiana.

31:44.236 --> 31:48.198
I want her to know that
her own happiness is important.

31:49.825 --> 31:53.161
And that's the story
that you're writing for Theo.

31:56.665 --> 31:58.083
Cheers to that.

32:00.335 --> 32:02.379
Gotta love root beer.

32:02.379 --> 32:04.548
Well, you know
that's a twist cap, right?

32:04.548 --> 32:06.007
Oh, yeah, I know.

32:06.007 --> 32:07.717
But you're gonna want
to use that move

32:07.717 --> 32:09.386
when you start dating again,

32:09.386 --> 32:11.221
'cause it never fails
to impress the ladies.

32:11.221 --> 32:13.056
[ Chuckles ] Uh‐huh.

32:13.056 --> 32:17.060
So, you and the girlfriend
with the broken light bulb ‐‐

32:17.060 --> 32:18.478
you guys make it?

32:18.478 --> 32:20.230
[ Chuckles ] Nah.

32:20.230 --> 32:21.773
I mean,
we tried at first.

32:21.773 --> 32:23.483
It was her way of dealing
with the guilt.

32:23.483 --> 32:24.985
Mm.
But, ultimately,

32:24.985 --> 32:26.820
life with a partner
who uses a chair

32:26.820 --> 32:29.656
just wasn't the way she played
Barbies when she was little.

32:29.656 --> 32:31.658
Well, I'm sorry.

32:31.658 --> 32:33.243
Well, I'm not.

32:33.243 --> 32:34.536
If we'd stayed together
in the long run,

32:34.536 --> 32:36.788
I'd be dealing with a wheelchair
and alimony.

32:36.788 --> 32:38.123
[ Chuckles ]

32:40.000 --> 32:42.127
How are you so okay
with all of this?

32:42.127 --> 32:45.088
Oh, I have my bad days.

32:45.088 --> 32:47.132
I mean, look, man,
having to use a wheelchair ‐‐

32:47.132 --> 32:49.676
yeah, it can totally suck
sometimes.

32:49.676 --> 32:51.678
Everyday things that you used
to take for granted

32:51.678 --> 32:53.889
are so much harder now.

32:53.889 --> 32:57.517
But...I love what I do.

32:57.517 --> 32:59.227
And I don't know if
that would have been the case

32:59.227 --> 33:01.146
if I didn't get injured.

33:01.146 --> 33:03.148
So, now I get
to spend my life

33:03.148 --> 33:04.649
helping people
get their lives back.

33:06.985 --> 33:10.530
Speaking of,
from what Darcy tells me ‐‐

33:10.530 --> 33:13.575
yeah, you've been in
recovery phase one long enough.

33:13.575 --> 33:15.285
It's time for phase two.

33:15.285 --> 33:16.620
What is phase two?

33:16.620 --> 33:17.871
Get a job.

33:17.871 --> 33:20.290
Something out in the world
that's low‐stakes.

33:20.290 --> 33:23.543
You just want to clock in,
clock out, build confidence.

33:23.543 --> 33:25.879
[ Exhales ]

33:25.879 --> 33:27.464
Start looking
at the future.

33:27.464 --> 33:34.262
♪♪

33:34.262 --> 33:38.850
Well, it was a rocky start,
but we found our way.

33:38.850 --> 33:41.937
I want to thank Jonah
for being so brave,

33:41.937 --> 33:45.232
and, in doing so,
helping me to be brave.

33:45.232 --> 33:48.360
This has been
"In the Room With Dr. Bloom."

33:48.360 --> 33:49.736
Talk to you tomorrow.

33:52.489 --> 33:53.740
[ Click ]

33:56.284 --> 33:58.286
[ Laughs ]

33:58.286 --> 33:59.663
You can't just cancel
my segment.

33:59.663 --> 34:00.997
What was that ‐‐
some kind of ratings ploy?

34:00.997 --> 34:02.332
No, of course not.

34:02.332 --> 34:04.542
There was a child
that needed my help.

34:04.542 --> 34:05.961
That doesn't give you a right
to break the rules.

34:05.961 --> 34:07.754
Well,
what should I have done?

34:07.754 --> 34:09.464
Told him
to call back tomorrow?

34:09.464 --> 34:10.966
It was important.

34:10.966 --> 34:12.384
So was traffic
and weather.

34:12.384 --> 34:14.094
Okay, well, if somebody needs
to know it's raining,

34:14.094 --> 34:16.221
they can look outside.

34:16.221 --> 34:19.099
I've done six reports
in the morning

34:19.099 --> 34:21.268
and six in the afternoon

34:21.268 --> 34:24.521
every single weekday
for the last two years.

34:24.521 --> 34:26.189
People depend on it.

34:26.189 --> 34:27.440
The mom who's rushing
from a meeting

34:27.440 --> 34:29.693
to get
to her kid's soccer game?

34:29.693 --> 34:32.570
If she doesn't know to take
side streets and avoid Route 9,

34:32.570 --> 34:34.155
she's gonna be late,

34:34.155 --> 34:35.615
sending a message
to her kid

34:35.615 --> 34:38.910
that he's not the most important
thing in her life.

34:38.910 --> 34:40.787
What I do matters.

34:40.787 --> 34:45.959
♪♪

34:45.959 --> 34:47.002
[ Door opens ]

34:47.002 --> 34:48.837
You're right.

34:48.837 --> 34:50.130
I'm sorry.

34:51.589 --> 34:54.009
I didn't think about it
that way.

34:54.009 --> 35:00.348
♪♪

35:00.348 --> 35:01.933
Is the kid okay?

35:03.435 --> 35:06.688
Yeah, I, uh, connected
with his uncle

35:06.688 --> 35:09.774
and got them some resources
they need to get help.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.068
Good.

35:13.528 --> 35:15.822
But don't ever do that
to me again.

35:15.822 --> 35:17.407
[ Door closes ]

35:17.407 --> 35:19.326
♪♪

35:19.326 --> 35:21.911
Yeah, I know
it was a long day for you.

35:21.911 --> 35:23.079
[ Car alarm chirps ]

35:23.079 --> 35:24.623
But you're gonna love
this new place.

35:24.623 --> 35:26.791
[ Chuckles ]
So much grass.

35:26.791 --> 35:29.002
Basically a Phish concert.

35:29.002 --> 35:30.670
Oh.

35:38.887 --> 35:40.764
[ Seat belt clicks ]

35:40.764 --> 35:43.058
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:43.058 --> 35:45.352
We need to talk.

35:45.352 --> 35:47.228
♪♪

35:51.524 --> 35:53.443
What the hell
are you doing here?

35:53.443 --> 35:54.611
You know we can't be
seen together.

35:54.611 --> 35:56.196
Please ‐‐
Please, just give me a minute.

35:56.196 --> 35:58.156
We need to talk.
No, we don't.

35:58.156 --> 35:59.866
We had a plan.
This isn't it.

35:59.866 --> 36:02.285
I want you to look at me!

36:02.285 --> 36:05.872
Tell me what you did
to my daughter.

36:05.872 --> 36:06.956
Did you hurt her?

36:06.956 --> 36:08.249
No, no, I ‐‐

36:10.543 --> 36:12.295
I would never ‐‐ never ‐‐

36:12.295 --> 36:13.963
I would never hurt Layla.

36:13.963 --> 36:15.674
I swear to you.

36:15.674 --> 36:17.050
I‐I loved her.

36:17.050 --> 36:18.009
You what?!

36:18.009 --> 36:20.845
You didn't love
my daughter!

36:20.845 --> 36:23.056
I love my daughter,
I love my daughter,

36:23.056 --> 36:24.224
and you took her away
from me.

36:24.224 --> 36:25.725
No. No, I didn't.

36:25.725 --> 36:28.395
You took everything
away from me.

36:28.395 --> 36:30.063
Aah!

36:30.063 --> 36:32.941
Hey, hey, hey!
Easy. Remember the plan.

36:32.941 --> 36:34.859
I don't care!
I don't care!

36:34.859 --> 36:36.319
Did you hear
what he just said?

36:36.319 --> 36:37.904
He did this to her.
He got in her head.

36:37.904 --> 36:39.155
He was the reason
she ‐‐

36:39.155 --> 36:43.368
♪♪

36:43.368 --> 36:44.619
Go home.

36:44.619 --> 36:47.706
♪♪

36:47.706 --> 36:48.748
Christopher.

36:51.543 --> 36:55.422
I'm gonna get him to tell me
what he did to my daughter,

36:55.422 --> 36:57.841
and that's between him and me
and no one else.

36:59.592 --> 37:01.428
Go home.

37:01.428 --> 37:09.269
♪♪

37:09.269 --> 37:10.937
After you went home,

37:10.937 --> 37:13.440
I got him to tell me...

37:13.440 --> 37:15.859
what he did to Layla.

37:15.859 --> 37:17.152
And I just ‐‐

37:17.152 --> 37:19.112
[ Breathes shakily ]

37:19.112 --> 37:20.864
I just lost it.

37:20.864 --> 37:22.741
Something in me snapped.
I couldn't help it.

37:24.367 --> 37:25.827
What do we do?

37:25.827 --> 37:27.036
"Do"?
We do nothing.

37:27.036 --> 37:29.038
We keep our heads down.

37:29.038 --> 37:30.874
But I can't stop thinking
about it,

37:30.874 --> 37:33.418
and I'm worried that
Georgia can tell that
something is going on.

37:33.418 --> 37:36.004
That's because you're
acting like something
is going on.

37:37.297 --> 37:41.426
You know how Peter
did what he did to
Layla and Sophie

37:41.426 --> 37:43.303
